  "prompt": "Do chipmunks bite people?",
  "response": "Yes, chipmunks can bite people, but it is relatively rare and usually occurs only when the chipmunk feels threatened or cornered. Chipmunks are generally shy, small rodents that prefer to avoid humans. However, if someone tries to handle or capture a chipmunk, it may bite in self-defense.\n\nIt's important to remember that chipmunks, like other wild animals, can carry diseases such as rabies (though this is rare in chipmunks) and other infections. Therefore, it's best to admire chipmunks from a distance and avoid attempting to touch or feed them. If bitten, clean the wound thoroughly and seek medical advice if necessary.",
